senior leadership  greycastle holdings ltd senior leadership lord james blyth chairman lord james blyth has served in senior positions in both the public and private sectors in the uk he was chairman of diageo plc the world’s leading premium drinks business from  to  he is currently a senior advisor to greenhill  co inc having been vicechairman and is a director of anixter inc lord blyth joined the boots company plc in october  as chief executive and became chairman in   he retired from this position in july  from july  until the general election in may  he served as chairman of the prime minister’s advisory panel on the citizen’s charter  he was a governor of the london business school from  until  and was made an honorary fellow in july   he was made an honorary doctor of laws by nottingham university in july  he has been a nonexecutive director of the imperial group cadbury schweppes british aerospace and nat west group  he was vicechairman of middlebrook pharmaceuticals inc lord blyth was educated at spiers school and glasgow university ma hons he was knighted in  and awarded a life peerage in    raymond brooks chief executive officer raymond brooks has more than two decades of experience in risk management capital markets and portfolio management he led aca financial guaranty corporation’s  billion runoff liquidation as its ceo from august  through september  in connection with its global restructuring over that period he increased surplus value by growing assets by  while running off insured liabilities by  additionally he discovered and preserved strategic net operating losses of  million previously he was managing director of alvarez  marsal advising insurers and creditors on balance sheet issues and ceo and founder of pine creek capital a manager of debt and structured financial products he has held positions at price waterhouse lehman bros and aubrey g lanstonindustrial bank of japan and served as a member of the chicago mercantile exchange and the interna